<div id="review_3585271787" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3585271787" />
    <a title="Catherine" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/799862-catherine"><img alt="Catherine" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1574793310p2/799862.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3585271787?book_show_action=true">Oct 07, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Catherine" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Catherine" href="/user/show/799862-catherine">Catherine</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3585271787" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer17970953519545558925">Beautifully written, rather depressing literary short stories about people and life between the world wars in England and Ireland. I had thought, mistakenly as it turns out, that I was getting ghost stories since she wrote those as well. &quot;The Demon Lover&quot; is utterly chilling and there are ghostly elements in some of the other stories, but the other stories were mostly not my jam, hence the lower number of stars. You might like her more literary work if you&apos;re a fan of precursors to Shirley Jacks</span>
  <span id="freeText17970953519545558925" style="display:none">Beautifully written, rather depressing literary short stories about people and life between the world wars in England and Ireland. I had thought, mistakenly as it turns out, that I was getting ghost stories since she wrote those as well. "The Demon Lover" is utterly chilling and there are ghostly elements in some of the other stories, but the other stories were mostly not my jam, hence the lower number of stars. You might like her more literary work if you're a fan of precursors to Shirley Jackson, perhaps, but she doesn't have quite the same edge. Interesting slice of life, vivid descriptions, lovely writing, however.</span>
  <a data-text-id="17970953519545558925" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


