          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Hardcover 9780394516660" href="/book/show/2614972-the-collected-stories-of-elizabeth-bowen">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2142990551" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer10044137362697332000">These short stories were very detailed and pretty interesting. Every time I took a second to think I was amazed at how delicate and fragile the writing seemed and how detailed it was. Elizabeth Bowen was a talented writer. I could imagine these stories weren’t stories but real people experiencing real things. But they were just stories. Are they? Is there a such thing as just a story? </span>

          </span>
        </div>


